<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Tiger" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Tiger,</orth> the animal Felis tigris; proverbially ferocious: <bibl n="shak. ven 1096" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1096</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 955" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 955</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 955" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 955</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 19.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 19, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 2, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.233" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 233</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.260" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 260</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.137" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.137" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 137</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.50" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.84" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.4.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 4, 31</bibl> <cit><quote>(a male t.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 54</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 54</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.5" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.189" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 189</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.4.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 4, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 33</bibl>. Unchanged in the fem. (the form <emph>tigress</emph> unknown to Sh.): <cit><quote>when did the --'s young ones teach the dam?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 142</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that heinous t. Tamora,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.195" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 195</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--s, not daughters,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 40</bibl></cit>.<lb />Name of an inn: <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 95</bibl>. of a ship: <bibl n="shak. tn 5.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 7</bibl>.
